'''詛咒娃娃'''又稱'''鬼娃'''，是一個[[都會傳奇|都市传说]]的題材，內容是關於平常隨處可見的[[玩偶|玩偶]]忽然會有自己的意識開始自由行動的故事，娃娃甚至可以傷人或是殺人，因為相關的事物常見，所造成的後果卻很可怕，常作為[[恐怖電影|恐怖電影]]的題材。
==概述==
玩具复活的桥段在历史上的[[儿童文学|儿童文学]]中已多次出现，而如今这个概念广泛的被应用到[[恐怖电影|恐怖电影]]和恐怖文学中。<ref>{{citation |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nme7AAAAIAAJ&pg=PA34 |title=Media Myths, Children's Nightmares |quote=Stories of toys that come to life can of course be found throughout the history of children's literature...|isbn=9780719045950 |last1=Buckingham |first1=David |year=1996 }}</ref>1978年的电影《魔法》是后来恐怖诅咒娃娃类型电影的主要灵感来源，而这一流派中最著名的则是儿童戏剧电影。<ref>{{cite book | last=Buckingham | first=David | year=1996 | title=Moving Images: Understanding Children's Emotional Responses to Television | publisher=Manchester University Press | isbn=978-0-7190-4595-0 | page=[https://archive.org/details/movingimagesunde0000buck/page/34 34] | url=https://archive.org/details/movingimagesunde0000buck/page/34 }}</ref><ref name="lennard1">Lennard, Dominic W. [http://www.tandfonline.com/doi/full/10.1080/10304312.2012.630142 All fun and games…: children's culture in the horror film, from Deep Red (1975) to Child's Play (1988)], ''[[Continuum:_Journal_of_Media_&_Cultural_Studies|Continuum: Journal of Media & Cultural Studies]]'', Vol. 26, No. 1, pp. 133-142 (2012)</ref>

其中几集作品里，表现了使用[[腹语术|腹语术]]的表演者操纵假人玩偶的景象，在这些景象里，玩偶不由自主的被摆弄，做出各种形式的动作，有时候甚至逼真到就像真的是活人一样。<ref name=io9vent>{{cite web|last1=Trendacosta|first1=Katherine|title=The 10 Creepiest Ventriloquist Dummies of All Time|url=http://io9.com/the-10-creepiest-ventriloquist-dummies-of-all-time-458555695|website=io9|accessdate=12 October 2015|date=25 March 2013|archive-date=2015-12-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151202034726/http://io9.com/the-10-creepiest-ventriloquist-dummies-of-all-time-458555695|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==著名的詛咒娃娃==
;[[安娜貝爾娃娃|安娜貝爾娃娃]]
:一個{{Link-en|拉基迪·安|Raggedy Ann}}[[娃娃|娃娃]]，[[美國|美國]]{{link-en|靈探|Ghost hunting|靈異現象調查者}}[[華倫夫婦|華倫夫婦]]將其認定為[[詛咒娃娃|詛咒娃娃]]。娃娃目前位於[[康乃狄克州|康乃狄克州]][[門羅_(康乃狄克州)|門羅]]，被安置在華倫夫婦的靈異博物館中的玻璃櫃內<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.warrens.net/Annabelle.html|title=Annabelle|website=www.warrens.net|access-date=2017-11-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160522230945/http://www.warrens.net/annabelle.html|archive-date=2016-05-22|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref name="usat_'Ann">{{Cite web| title = 'Annabelle' joins ranks of freaky dolls in horror films| author = Bryan Alexander| work = USA TODAY| date = 2014-10-01| accessdate = 2015-03-11| url = https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/movies/2014/10/01/dolls-creepy-annabelle/15474915/| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150223083605/http://www.usatoday.com/story/life/movies/2014/10/01/dolls-creepy-annabelle/15474915/| archive-date = 2015-02-23| dead-url = no}}</ref><ref name="glam_TheR">{{Cite web| title = The Real-Life Story Behind Annabelle Is Even More Bone-Chilling Than the Movie| last = Eidell| first = Lynsey| work = Glamour| date = 2014-10-07| accessdate = 2015-03-11| url = http://www.glamour.com/entertainment/blogs/obsessed/2014/10/real-story-behind-annabelle| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150315031542/http://www.glamour.com/entertainment/blogs/obsessed/2014/10/real-story-behind-annabelle| archive-date = 2015-03-15| dead-url = no}}</ref><ref name="yaho_Howt">{{Cite web| title = How the Real Doll Behind 'Annabelle' Became Even Freakier for the Movies| author = Joal Ryan| work = Yahoo!| date = 2014-10-03| accessdate = 2015-03-11| url = https://www.yahoo.com/movies/how-the-real-doll-behind-annabelle-became-even-99081889057.html| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150129113222/https://www.yahoo.com/movies/how-the-real-doll-behind-annabelle-became-even-99081889057.html| archive-date = 2015-01-29| dead-url = no}}</ref><ref name="Travel Channel">{{cite episode|url=http://www.travelchannel.com/video/annabelle-the-devil-doll|title=Annabelle the Devil Doll|series=Mysteries at the Museum|network=[[Travel_Channel|Travel Channel]]|host={{Link-en|唐·懷爾德曼|Don Wildman}}|accessdate=2014-12-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141126164429/http://www.travelchannel.com/video/annabelle-the-devil-doll|archive-date=2014-11-26|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在傑拉爾德·伯托（Gerald Brittle）所著的華倫夫婦傳記《The Demonologist》（2002年）中也有描述安娜貝爾娃娃的故事<ref name="Demonologist">{{cite book|title=The Demonologist: The Extraordinary Career of Ed and Lorraine Warren|first=Gerald|last=Brittle|publisher=iUniverse|date=2002-09-13|origyear=1980|isbn=978-0-595-24618-2|chapterurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=0qscomSDhcoC&pg=PA39|chapter=Annabelle|pages=39–53|access-date=2019-04-05|archive-date=2020-12-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201206180308/https://books.google.com/books?id=0qscomSDhcoC&pg=PA39|dead-url=no}}</ref>。安娜貝爾娃娃常被拿來和另一個知名{{Link-en|鬧鬼娃娃|Haunted doll}}「[[羅伯特娃娃|羅伯特娃娃]]」相提並論<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ihorror.com/meet-robert-creepy-doll-inspired-childs-play/|title=Meet Robert; The Haunted Doll That Inspired Child’s Play|website=ihorror.com|date=2014-12-03|access-date=2019-04-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190103114356/https://www.ihorror.com/meet-robert-creepy-doll-inspired-childs-play/|archive-date=2019-01-03|dead-url=no}}</ref>。
:根據華倫夫婦所言，美國一位讀護理的學生唐娜·詹寧斯（Donna Jennings）於1968年取得了這個娃娃，據說這個娃娃有一些怪異舉動。有位[[靈媒|靈媒]]告訴唐娜，娃娃體內寄宿著一名叫「安娜貝爾」的死去女孩的靈魂。知道這點後，唐娜和她的室友試圖要接納這個娃娃，但娃娃卻做出了一些駭人的惡意行為。此時，唐娜和她的室友決定要求助於華倫夫婦，前來了解案情的華倫夫婦稱這個娃娃已被{{Link-en|邪靈附身|Demonic possession}}，並將娃娃搬移到自家的博物館中。
:娃娃的故事成為了電影《[[厲陰宅|厲陰宅]]》（2013年）開場場景的靈感，之後更被改編為[[厲陰宅系列電影|系列電影]]《[[安娜貝爾_(電影)|安娜貝爾]]》（2014年）、《[[安娜貝爾：造孽|安娜貝爾：造孽]]》（2017年）和《[[安娜貝爾回家囉|安娜貝爾回家囉]]》（2019年）。電影中娃娃的形象也曾短暫出現在電影《[[厲陰宅2|厲陰宅2]]》（2016年）、《[[水行俠_(電影)|水行俠]]》（2018年）和《[[沙贊！_(電影)|沙贊！]]》（2019年）的場景中<ref>{{cite web|url=https://screenrant.com/aquaman-movie-annabelle-easter-egg-james-wan/|title=The Evil Annabelle Doll Makes a Cameo in James Wan's Aquaman Movie|website=ScreenRant|first=Christopher|last=Fiduccia|date=2018-12-06|accessdate=2018-12-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190101051458/https://screenrant.com/aquaman-movie-annabelle-easter-egg-james-wan/|archive-date=2019-01-01|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/04/05/shazam-end-credits-scene-explained-post-credits-scene-mister-mind-caterpillar-worm-spoilers|title=Shazam! End Credits Scene Explained|website=IGN|first=Jim|last=Vejvoda|date=2019年4月5日|accessdate=2019-04-05|archive-date=2019-04-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190406164627/https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/04/05/shazam-end-credits-scene-explained-post-credits-scene-mister-mind-caterpillar-worm-spoilers|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

;[[羅伯特娃娃|羅伯特娃娃]]
:最初屬於Robert Eugene Otto。據報導，該娃娃由[[德國|德國]]的Steiff公司製造，由Otto的祖父在1904年前往德國時購買，並作為生日禮物送給年輕的Otto。根據傳說，羅伯特娃娃具有[[超自然|超自然]]的能力，可以移動，改變它的面部表情，並發出咯咯的聲音。根據當地民間傳說，羅伯特娃娃已經造成車禍，骨折，失業，離婚和其他不幸。該娃娃目前在{{link-en|基韋斯特藝術與歷史博物館|Martello Gallery-Key West Art and Historical Museum|基韋斯特藝術與歷史博物館}}展出。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slate.com/blogs/atlas_obscura/2013/11/18/robert_the_haunted_doll_creeping_out_floridians_since_1904.html|title=Robert the Haunted Doll: Creeping Out Floridians Since 1904|author=Ella Morton|publisher=Slate.com|date=2013-11-18}}</ref>

;曼迪
:於1910年至1920年間在英國或德國製造，1991年捐贈給不列顛哥倫比亞省Quesnel博物館，據稱具有超自然力量，眼睛會跟隨博物館參觀者。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2018/10/31/haunted-doll-canada_a_23577068/|title=Canada Is Home To One Of The World's Most Famous Haunted Dolls|date=2018-10-31|website=HuffPost Canada|language=en|access-date=2019-03-30}}</ref>

;菊子
:據說1918年日本一個名叫鈴木英吉的少年從北海道為他的妹妹菊子買的娃娃。菊子死後她的家人相信菊子的靈魂在娃娃身上，而娃娃的頭髮不斷長。這個娃娃現在安置在北海道的萬念寺。<ref name="Ross2011">{{cite book|author=Catrien Ross|title=Japanese Ghost Stories: Spirits, Hauntings, and Paranormal Phenomena|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=yYLQAgAAQBAJ&pg=PT82|date=30 August 2011|publisher=Tuttle Publishing|isbn=978-1-4629-0100-5|pages=82–}}</ref>

